681
00:53:58.920 --> 00:54:01.275
I'm a bad parent because I hate my kid?

682
00:54:01.440 --> 00:54:04.910
- There is something strange about that boy!
- He is twisted!

683
00:54:05.080 --> 00:54:08.231
- You took him! He's yours!
- You conned us into it!

684
00:54:08.400 --> 00:54:13.554
What am I supposed to do with the little
creep? He's already been returned 30 times!

685
00:54:13.720 --> 00:54:15.836
This makes 31!

686
00:54:16.000 --> 00:54:18.594
"We don't care about
brown hair and brown eyes."

687
00:54:18.760 --> 00:54:22.196
"We want to take him into our home
and let him play with our cat!"

688
00:54:22.360 --> 00:54:24.749
Hold it! Stop. wait!

689
00:54:24.920 --> 00:54:28.595
What are we talking about?
Thirty? Thirty times?

690
00:54:28.760 --> 00:54:31.149
Flo. did you hear that?

691
00:54:31.320 --> 00:54:33.834
This is a human being
we're talking about!

692
00:54:34.000 --> 00:54:36.275
That kid's a monster!

693
00:54:36.440 --> 00:54:40.228
Flo. we're doing what everybody
else has done to this child.

694
00:54:40.400 --> 00:54:43.676
- It's easy to give up on a kid.
- Damn straight it is.

695
00:54:43.840 --> 00:54:48.960
Isn't that what's wrong with the world today?
Everybody's looking for the easy way out.

696
00:54:49.120 --> 00:54:53.955
They're hoping that their
problems will just go away.

697
00:54:54.120 --> 00:54:58.113
But problems don't
just go. Flo. you know?

698
00:54:58.280 --> 00:55:02.796
So. the question before us is what are
we gonna do with our little problem child?

699
00:55:02.960 --> 00:55:05.076
I'll tell you.

700
00:55:05.240 --> 00:55:10.234
Something that no one's ever done for
him before. We're gonna love him. Flo.

701
00:55:11.320 --> 00:55:15.552
We're gonna love him when he's bad.
we're gonna love him when he's worse.

702
00:55:15.720 --> 00:55:19.713
until one day he's gonna crack and say.

703
00:55:19.880 --> 00:55:23.953
"Hey. these folks really do love me."

704
00:55:24.120 --> 00:55:26.395
"They ain't gonna quit on me."

705
00:55:26.560 --> 00:55:29.518
"I don't have to be bad any more."

706
00:55:29.680 --> 00:55:33.593
"What the hay! I can be
president of the United States!"

707
00:55:34.240 --> 00:55:39.553
President? Are you brain damaged? Junior's
gonna be a convict before he's in third grade!

708
00:55:39.720 --> 00:55:41.199
Sh!

709
00:55:41.360 --> 00:55:43.590
Junior? Son?

710
00:55:45.000 --> 00:55:48.356
- Unlock the door.
- You said you were gonna keep me forever.

711
00:55:49.680 --> 00:55:52.752
I am. I'm sorry. I just made a mistake.

712
00:55:52.920 --> 00:55:56.515
Trust me. We're not gonna
take you back to the orphanage.

713
00:55:56.680 --> 00:56:01.674
I don't believe you! You only pretended to
be my friend. You're just like all the others.

714
00:56:03.320 --> 00:56:06.357
Junior? Now. come on. son.

715
00:56:07.920 --> 00:56:10.559
You moron. You left the keys in the car.

716
00:56:11.600 --> 00:56:15.195
Hey. he can drive! Boy. that's great!

717
00:56:15.880 --> 00:56:19.759
Look at you handle this baby!
I'm so proud of you. son!

718
00:56:21.000 --> 00:56:22.797
Junior!

719
00:56:22.960 --> 00:56:25.793
Hold it!

720
00:56:26.920 --> 00:56:28.592
Get out of the way!

721
00:56:29.240 --> 00:56:31.231
Left! Turn left!

722
00:56:32.160 --> 00:56:34.879
Right. Junior.

723
00:56:37.760 --> 00:56:41.514
No!

724
00:56:41.680 --> 00:56:43.955
No. don't touch that!

725
00:56:45.800 --> 00:56:48.030
Junior!

726
00:56:58.960 --> 00:57:00.712
Watch out!

727
00:57:07.120 --> 00:57:10.556
<i>Born to be wild</i>

728
00:57:33.560 --> 00:57:34.879
Hello?

729
00:57:35.600 --> 00:57:37.955
Ben? Jim O'Connor. Are you sitting down?

730
00:57:38.120 --> 00:57:39.439
Yes.

731
00:57:39.600 --> 00:57:44.515
Bad news. Your father cleaned out your bank
account to pay for the damage to his store.

732
00:57:44.680 --> 00:57:47.877
Nothing can make up for the
loss of your life savings...

733
00:57:48.040 --> 00:57:49.359
Ben?

734
00:58:00.240 --> 00:58:02.231
<i>Uh-ohl He's lost it nowl</i>

735
00:58:16.320 --> 00:58:18.550
All right!

736
00:58:23.040 --> 00:58:25.270
Private business.

737
00:58:25.440 --> 00:58:27.078
Hi!

738
00:58:27.240 --> 00:58:32.394
- Get out of my way. kid. I'm looking for JR.
- That's me! Junior!

739
00:58:36.080 --> 00:58:39.231
I don't have time for this crap. kid.

740
00:58:39.400 --> 00:58:44.155
Now. the guy I'm looking for is an
ex-con and he's as mean as a rattlesnake.

741
00:58:44.320 --> 00:58:47.392
That's me. dummy! I sent
you all those letters.

742
00:58:47.560 --> 00:58:53.157
Man. I drove a thousand miles to
hang out with a seven- year-old?

743
00:58:53.320 --> 00:58:56.995
- I'm gonna be eight in two weeks.
- Don't count on it.

744
00:59:01.320 --> 00:59:06.599
Mr Healy. Mrs Healy. I'd like you to meet
the greatest guy in the whole wide world.

745
00:59:06.760 --> 00:59:08.398
Martin...

746
00:59:09.960 --> 00:59:11.757
Uncle Marty!

747
00:59:11.920 --> 00:59:14.229
Marty. this is Mr and Mrs Healy

748
00:59:14.400 --> 00:59:18.234
and that's the $3.000 stereo
system and the console TV.

749
00:59:18.400 --> 00:59:20.277
How wonderful. an uncle!

750
00:59:20.440 --> 00:59:22.795
You absolutely must stay the night.

751
00:59:22.960 --> 00:59:26.430
It is so wonderful to meet the
uncle of darling little Junior.

752
00:59:26.600 --> 00:59:31.037
Did you hear that? Uncle Marty. We've
gotta treat this guy like royalty.

753
00:59:31.200 --> 00:59:36.274
We've gotta make him think Junior's an angel.
He'll leave and take the little brat with him.

754
00:59:36.440 --> 00:59:39.159
Everybody just loves Junior.

755
00:59:39.320 --> 00:59:43.996
For pocket money he helps some of the
older residents with their groceries.

756
00:59:44.160 --> 00:59:45.957
Isn't that right. Ben?

757
00:59:48.080 --> 00:59:54.030
If only he had a blood relative taking care of
him. someone with a natural tie. Like an uncle!

758
00:59:54.200 --> 00:59:56.270
- More meatloaf?
- Yeah.

759
00:59:56.440 --> 00:59:58.351
I'll get you some.

760
00:59:58.520 --> 01:00:01.353
<i>This guy is just so appealing.</i>

761
01:00:01.520 --> 01:00:03.829
I'll give you a hand.

762
01:00:06.480 --> 01:00:11.634
Your nephew is such a delight. He's always
cleaning and tidying up after all of us.

763
01:00:11.800 --> 01:00:14.155
Perfect for a single man living alone.

764
01:00:14.320 --> 01:00:16.311
Are you a bachelor. Marty?

765
01:00:18.640 --> 01:00:21.757
I ain't been with a woman in 15 years.

766
01:00:21.920 --> 01:00:24.673
Women just love single male parents.

767
01:00:24.840 --> 01:00:29.356
If you had a kid like Junior the
women would be flocking over you.

768
01:00:39.160 --> 01:00:41.674
Did you say 15 years?

769
01:00:43.320 --> 01:00:45.311
Wait.

770
01:00:48.440 --> 01:00:51.512
Stop it!

771
01:01:22.280 --> 01:01:24.953
Look at all the stuff
I brought for our trip.

772
01:01:25.120 --> 01:01:30.592
I got my ammo. There's guns.
hand grenades and even dynamite.

773
01:01:33.800 --> 01:01:39.557
These are toys. What are you jerking
me around for? This is kiddies' stuff!

774
01:01:41.920 --> 01:01:45.549
What did you do that for?
Don't we need supplies?

775
01:01:45.720 --> 01:01:48.359
What? I'm not working with you!

776
01:01:49.080 --> 01:01:53.437
But I thought we were gonna be
partners. I thought you liked me.

777
01:01:53.600 --> 01:01:57.070
I don't like no one. I work alone.

778
01:02:00.040 --> 01:02:04.955
Goodbye. Junior! Goodbye. Flo!
Oh. I am so sad to see you go.

779
01:02:05.120 --> 01:02:08.749
A hundred thousand
dollars? You can keep 'em!

780
01:02:08.920 --> 01:02:11.992
Good morning! Hello. sunshine!

781
01:02:13.960 --> 01:02:16.190
This was supposed to be our honeymoon!

782
01:02:16.360 --> 01:02:19.750
You said you loved me! You
called me a little kumquat.

783
01:02:19.920 --> 01:02:22.514
This is our honeymoon. you moron!

784
01:02:22.680 --> 01:02:25.194
Moron? Moron?

785
01:02:25.360 --> 01:02:30.036
I went to Radcliffe! I'm not a bimbo
you can tie up and do what you want with!

786
01:02:30.200 --> 01:02:32.191
- You shut up!
- I will not!

787
01:02:32.360 --> 01:02:37.309
Let me out of here! You stupid
piece of... You're gonna regret this!

788
01:02:37.480 --> 01:02:42.429
I'm gonna be waiting and when I'm done
with you you're gonna be singing falsetto!

789
01:02:42.600 --> 01:02:46.275
He-e-e-ere's
Daddy!

790
01:02:48.920 --> 01:02:51.309
Goodbye. Junior!

791
01:02:51.480 --> 01:02:54.552
<i>Adiosl Hasta luegol</i>

792
01:02:55.720 --> 01:02:57.676
Sayonara!

793
01:02:58.680 --> 01:03:00.910
Yeah!

794
01:03:02.120 --> 01:03:04.873
Yes. that's very creative. Junior.

795
01:03:05.040 --> 01:03:07.679
Yeah. right on the money.

796
01:03:27.120 --> 01:03:29.554
He liked me.

797
01:03:29.720 --> 01:03:32.712
All this time he actually liked me.

798
01:03:44.520 --> 01:03:47.717
Vote for Big Ben. Here. read this.

799
01:03:50.640 --> 01:03:55.191
You can't go in. Your father's making a
television appearance for his campaign.

800
01:03:56.720 --> 01:03:58.950
Dad. I gotta talk to you!

801
01:03:59.120 --> 01:04:04.240
- What are you doing? I'm about to go on air!
- Florence and Junior have been kidnapped.

802
01:04:04.400 --> 01:04:05.753
Five minutes.

803
01:04:05.920 --> 01:04:08.275
- I need $100.000.
- Are you insane?

804
01:04:08.440 --> 01:04:13.719
That kid is a monster and your wife is the
original pain in the ass. It's for the best.

805
01:04:13.880 --> 01:04:17.350
- Are you gonna lend me the money?
- No. I'm not.

806
01:04:17.520 --> 01:04:21.195
You work for me. I know what
you get. You're a credit risk.

807
01:04:23.000 --> 01:04:24.991
Then I quit as your son!

808
01:04:25.160 --> 01:04:28.835
Just get out of here. I got
a goddamn campaign to win.

809
01:04:29.000 --> 01:04:33.073
Your campaign. the one
thing you do care about.

810
01:04:34.160 --> 01:04:38.551
Why don't you tell the voters what you
really plan on doing with this town?

811
01:04:38.720 --> 01:04:40.711
I don't give a rat's ass for the voters.

812
01:04:40.880 --> 01:04:45.237
<i>- We're ready with that live feed.
- All I care about is power and money.</i>

813
01:04:46.000 --> 01:04:50.118
<i>America for the Americansl
You believe that nonsense?</i>

814
01:04:50.280 --> 01:04:53.636
<i>I'd sell my soul to the Japanese
if they'd make me an offer.</i>

815
01:04:53.800 --> 01:04:56.917
<i>Don't come sucking round
me if you want something.</i>

816
01:04:57.080 --> 01:04:59.548
<i>The only thing you'll
get from me is this.</i>

817
01:05:18.040 --> 01:05:20.190
- Hello?
- You got the money?

818
01:05:20.960 --> 01:05:22.279
Yeah.

819
01:05:22.440 --> 01:05:25.591
Good. Bring it to the circus.

820
01:05:25.760 --> 01:05:28.513
I'll be waiting at the tiger cage.

821
01:05:30.800 --> 01:05:33.155
Roy! I need your car.

822
01:05:33.320 --> 01:05:36.232
- Forget it. We're going hunting.
- So am I.

823
01:05:36.400 --> 01:05:41.076
You can't borrow it. We're all packed
up and ready to go. What are you doing?

824
01:05:41.240 --> 01:05:43.231
You're not going anywhere. buddy.

825
01:05:45.200 --> 01:05:46.792
Wait a minute.

826
01:05:46.960 --> 01:05:49.190
Great. the joke's over. Come on back.

827
01:05:49.360 --> 01:05:51.351
What do you think you're doing?

828
01:05:55.880 --> 01:05:58.189
Hey! Hey. get back here. you!

829
01:06:01.440 --> 01:06:03.635
- What is he doing?
- Get back here!

830
01:06:05.320 --> 01:06:07.914
Gee. I've never been
to the circus before.

831
01:06:08.080 --> 01:06:11.595
- I'd sure like to try a swizzle dog.
- I hate circuses.

832
01:06:11.760 --> 01:06:15.673
Nothing worse than a bunch of
clowns trying to make you laugh.

833
01:06:24.080 --> 01:06:27.629
- Look. a giraffe!
- Look. a fist!

834
01:06:31.720 --> 01:06:33.915
Clowns.

835
01:06:34.080 --> 01:06:36.878
Help! Help. let me out of here!

836
01:06:37.040 --> 01:06:40.635
I know you're out there! Help!

837
01:06:40.800 --> 01:06:44.918
Why isn't anybody doing
anything? I know you're out there!

838
01:06:50.640 --> 01:06:52.835
Let's go see the bearded lady.

839
01:06:53.000 --> 01:06:57.471
I seen too many of them in prison. Stop
bugging me or you're gonna get hurt.

840
01:06:57.640 --> 01:07:01.474
What did you say. you
bow-tied freak? Let him go!

841
01:07:02.600 --> 01:07:04.397
Forget it. big daddy!

842
01:07:04.560 --> 01:07:07.358
This is my show. I'm calling the shots.

843
01:07:07.520 --> 01:07:11.479
OK. we make a switch
on the count of three.

844
01:07:11.640 --> 01:07:14.029
You toss the money and I release Junior.

845
01:07:14.200 --> 01:07:15.918
Fine.

846
01:07:16.080 --> 01:07:18.514
One. two. three!

847
01:07:19.040 --> 01:07:21.031
- Hey!
- Sucker!

848
01:07:21.200 --> 01:07:25.591
- Give me the boy!
- Why? He wants to go with me.

849
01:07:25.760 --> 01:07:30.675
How about it. kid? We'll go on a crime
spree. We'll terrorise the whole state.

850
01:07:30.840 --> 01:07:33.434
We'll eat smiley pies until we drop.

851
01:07:33.600 --> 01:07:35.909
What do you say?

852
01:07:37.640 --> 01:07:40.837
Come on. let's have
some kicks. Tell-a-me.

853
01:07:41.000 --> 01:07:42.672
Tell-a-me.

854
01:07:42.840 --> 01:07:44.796
Yeah. kicks. good idea.

855
01:07:50.880 --> 01:07:53.792
- I'll tear you apart!
- Not while I'm around!

856
01:07:54.840 --> 01:07:57.035
Run. Junior. run!

857
01:07:57.200 --> 01:07:59.395
My money!

858
01:08:04.640 --> 01:08:06.631
Hold it!

859
01:08:06.800 --> 01:08:11.920
<i>The astounding Aslanian Family Tumblersl</i>

860
01:08:41.040 --> 01:08:42.951
Excuse me. lady!

861
01:08:45.880 --> 01:08:47.791
Ye-es!

862
01:08:57.920 --> 01:09:00.275
I'll get you now!

863
01:09:12.760 --> 01:09:15.399
Look out below!

864
01:09:16.720 --> 01:09:19.234
- Junior. are you OK?
- Yeah. I'm fine. Dad.

865
01:09:20.720 --> 01:09:24.998
- You called me Dad.
- Yeah. I guess I did.

866
01:09:29.560 --> 01:09:31.198
Stay away from...

867
01:09:31.360 --> 01:09:35.433
- He's getting away!
- Nobody messes with the Healys! Come on!

868
01:09:37.520 --> 01:09:40.114
There he is!

869
01:09:40.280 --> 01:09:43.829
<i>There's nothing like going
for an outing with your father.</i>

870
01:09:44.000 --> 01:09:46.833
- Look what I found!
- That's Roy's. Give me that.

871
01:09:47.000 --> 01:09:49.036
Why? You can't drive and shoot.

872
01:09:49.200 --> 01:09:51.589
- What do we do?
- I got an idea.

873
01:09:54.200 --> 01:09:57.431
- Go get him. Dad!
- Faster. son. faster!

874
01:09:57.600 --> 01:09:59.989
Attaboy!

875
01:10:00.160 --> 01:10:02.515
Shoot out his tyres. Dad!

876
01:10:03.520 --> 01:10:05.431
Don't mess with me!

877
01:10:07.480 --> 01:10:10.040
I demand you stop this car!

878
01:10:12.360 --> 01:10:14.271
<i>He's the wild one</i>

879
01:10:14.440 --> 01:10:16.237
What the hell is going on?

880
01:10:16.400 --> 01:10:19.517
- I want a divorce!
- Shut up. Flo!

881
01:10:35.400 --> 01:10:37.391
Wha...!

882
01:10:39.040 --> 01:10:41.270
Stop! Hit the brakes!

883
01:10:55.680 --> 01:10:58.399
Now what's going on? What's that smell?

884
01:10:59.880 --> 01:11:02.474
Well. Flo always said
she wanted to travel.

885
01:11:05.320 --> 01:11:08.676
- Come on. let's go home.
- Move it.

886
01:11:11.840 --> 01:11:13.831
You little traitor!

887
01:11:14.000 --> 01:11:15.797
No!

888
01:11:20.680 --> 01:11:23.717
No!

889
01:11:25.720 --> 01:11:27.631
Daddy!

890
01:11:27.800 --> 01:11:31.952
Daddy. please don't go! I'm sorry
for all those bad things I did!

891
01:11:32.120 --> 01:11:36.238
If you come back. I promise I'll
never do anything naughty again.

892
01:11:36.400 --> 01:11:39.472
Daddy. come back! I love you!

893
01:11:41.360 --> 01:11:43.157
I love you. too. son.

894
01:11:43.320 --> 01:11:45.675
Dad? I don't believe it.

895
01:11:46.800 --> 01:11:48.870
I don't believe it either.

896
01:11:49.720 --> 01:11:51.950
- Are you gonna be OK?
- Yeah.

897
01:11:54.080 --> 01:11:56.548
But the prune's had it.

898
01:11:57.200 --> 01:12:00.237
- Lay still. Ambulance is on the way.
- I'll be all right.

899
01:12:00.400 --> 01:12:02.675
He got me in the prune.

900
01:12:03.400 --> 01:12:08.918
You're not gonna hold me to all that stupid
junk I said about being nice. are you?

901
01:12:09.080 --> 01:12:12.868
Of course not. I just
want you to be yourself.

902
01:12:13.920 --> 01:12:16.434
Some people never learn.

903
01:12:16.600 --> 01:12:18.750
Come on. son.

904
01:12:33.280 --> 01:12:34.679
Come on.

905
01:12:35.800 --> 01:12:39.873
<i>Why does this guy love me?
Why do parents love any kid?</i>

906
01:12:40.040 --> 01:12:45.717
<i>It's one of those answers we'll never know
like "How high is up?". "Why is the sky blue?"</i>

907
01:12:45.880 --> 01:12:48.269
<i>and "Whatever happened to Mrs Healy?"</i>

908
01:12:48.440 --> 01:12:53.753
- Your pig's making funny noises.
- Big Miguel. he's got a bad stomach.

909
01:12:58.120 --> 01:13:00.111
Oh. my God!

910
01:13:01.160 --> 01:13:05.278
<i>Na-na-na-na-na
Na-na-na-na-na</i>

911
01:13:05.440 --> 01:13:06.759
<i>N-
n-n- n-n-n-n-n</i>

912
01:13:06.920 --> 01:13:10.629
<i>Whoa-o-o-o-o</i>

913
01:13:10.800 --> 01:13:15.794
<i>Who wants to grow up?
Who wants responsibility?</i>

914
01:13:15.960 --> 01:13:19.191
<i>O-
o-o- e-e-e</i>

915
01:13:20.640 --> 01:13:25.839
<i>Who wants to show up
At work until you're 93?</i>

916
01:13:26.000 --> 01:13:29.197
<i>Oh. no. not me</i>

917
01:13:30.560 --> 01:13:35.395
